<div id="header">
<h1>Pygments</h1>
</div>
<div id="content">
<div id="preamble">
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p><a href="http://pygments.org/">Pygments</a> is a generic syntax highlighter.  Here is a <em>lexer</em> for highlighting
<a href="StandardML">Standard ML</a>.</p>
</div>
<div class="ulist">
<ul>
<li>
<p><a href="https://github.com/MLton/mlton/tree/master/ide/pygments/sml_lexer"><code>sml_lexer</code></a>&#8201;&#8212;&#8201;Provides highlighting of keywords, special constants, and (nested) comments.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect1">
<h2 id="_install_and_use">Install and use</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="ulist">
<ul>
<li>
<p>Checkout all files and install as a <a href="http://pygments.org/">Pygments</a> plugin.</p>
<div class="listingblock">
<div class="content">
<pre>$ git clone https://github.com/MLton/mlton.git mlton
$ cd mlton/ide/pygments
$ python setup.py install</pre>
</div>
</div>
</li>
<li>
<p>Invoke <code>pygmentize</code> with <code>-l sml</code>.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div>
